'''Fontamara''' is a 1977 Italian film, directed by [[Carlo Lizzani]] based on the [[Fontamara|novel of the same name]] by [[Ignazio Silone]].

It stars [[Michele Placido]] in the role of Berardo Viola and Antonella Murgia as Elvira.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fontamara (1981)|url=http://www.imdb.it/title/tt0076043/|accessdate=12 May 2011}}</ref> 

[[Ida Di Benedetto]] won the [[Nastro d'Argento]] (Silver Ribbon) for [[Nastro d'Argento Best supporting Actress|Best supporting Actress]] in 1981 for her supporting role as Maria Rosa.

